## Comparing a Staged File

### `git diff --staged filename.extension`

Shows staged changes that will be included in the next commit.

```bash
$ git diff --staged app.py
```

---

## Comparing All Staged Files

### `git diff --staged`

Shows staged changes for all files.

```bash
$ git diff --staged
```

---

## Comparing Two Commits

### `git diff hash1 hash2`

Shows differences between two commits.

```bash
$ git diff a3f5c1d 8f3e2c1
```

---

### `git diff HEAD~1 HEAD`

Compares the latest commit with its previous commit.

```bash
$ git diff HEAD~1 HEAD
```

`HEAD` refers to the current commit, while `HEAD~1` refers to its parent commit.